py-ovs
======
Simple voting system using Python and Textual
library. It uses MongoDB for its database.

Installation
============
1. Clone the repository
2. I highly suggests that you create a virtual environment
   inside the repo

   Run the following:
   -------------------- 
   python -m venv .venv
   --------------------
   
   To activate the virtual environment,
   
   Run the following
   If using windows command-line:
   --------------------------
   .venv\Scripts\activate
   --------------------------
   
   If using Linux/UNIX-like environment:
   -------------------------
   source .venv/bin/activate
   -------------------------

3. Install the requirements by running
   -------------------------------
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   -------------------------------

4. Inside the src folder, change the .env.example name to
   ".env" and change the value of MONGO_URI inside of it
   to your MongoDB URI [1].


